WEBVTT

00:00.083 --> 00:02.561
Wait for it...
Wait for it...

00:02.562 --> 00:03.996
<i>9:01!</i>

00:03.997 --> 00:06.999
Amy Santiago is officially
late for the first time ever.

00:07.000 --> 00:09.034
All right, let's do this.
Who's got theories?

00:09.035 --> 00:11.069
Uh...
Alarm didn't go off.

00:11.070 --> 00:12.704
All three alarms?
All with battery back-up?

00:12.705 --> 00:14.971
Come on, who wants
to take this seriously?

00:14.972 --> 00:16.708
Ooh!
She was taken in her sleep!

00:16.709 --> 00:18.143
That's what I'm talking about!

00:18.144 --> 00:19.811
Super dark, Boyle,
but way more plausible

00:19.812 --> 00:22.395
than the sarge's idiotic
alarm clock theory.

00:22.396 --> 00:24.082
I bet she tucked herself
into bed too tight

00:24.083 --> 00:25.250
and got stuck.

00:25.251 --> 00:26.985
Mm, maybe she Fell
into another dimension

00:26.986 --> 00:28.693
where she's interesting.

00:28.694 --> 00:31.390
It's 9:00 A.M.
why is no one working?

00:31.391 --> 00:33.025
Amy Santiago is
a few minutes late,

00:33.026 --> 00:34.660
and we're all trying
to guess why.

00:34.661 --> 00:36.728
I'd like to play.

00:36.729 --> 00:41.400
I'd say she's in line
at the bank.

00:41.401 --> 00:43.101
This is fun.
<i>(Jake) It is fun,</i>

00:43.102 --> 00:45.127
<i>but you're
all wrong.</i>

00:45.128 --> 00:47.272
She clearly slipped through
a subway grate

00:47.273 --> 00:50.006
and is having terrible sex
with a mole man.

00:50.007 --> 00:51.254
[Elevator dings]

00:51.255 --> 00:52.945
<i>(Jake) There she is.
Amy.</i>

00:52.946 --> 00:54.379
Where have you been?

00:54.380 --> 00:56.648
We've been worried sick.
Do you care to explain yourself?

00:56.649 --> 00:58.383
I'm just 70 seconds late.
It's not a big deal.

00:58.384 --> 01:00.182
Don't worry about it.

01:00.188 --> 01:03.722
Santiago, you will tell us,
and you will tell us now.

01:03.723 --> 01:05.397
There was a problem
at the bank.

01:05.397 --> 01:06.992
Hot damn!

